  "text": "The Type class hierarchy is defined in llvm/include/llvm/IR/DerivedTypes.h (IntegerType, FunctionType, StructType declarations) and implemented in llvm/lib/IR/Type.cpp (factory methods like IntegerType::get, FunctionType::get, StructType::get/create). Context ownership is managed through LLVMContextImpl (llvm/lib/IR/LLVMContextImpl.h) which holds the DenseMap<unsigned, IntegerType*> IntegerTypes and similar type caches, with LLVMContext.cpp and LLVMContextImpl.cpp providing the public API and lifecycle management. The IR-to-machine-type lowering flows through: (1) ValueTypes.cpp providing MVT::getVT (IR Type -> MVT) and EVT::getTypeForEVT (EVT -> IR Type) bidirectional conversion, (2) TargetLoweringBase.cpp implementing getTypeConversion for type legalization decisions, (3) SelectionDAGBuilder.cpp calling ComputeValueVTs and TLI.getRegisterType to lower IR types to SelectionDAG value types, (4) LegalizeTypes.cpp running DAGTypeLegalizer to legalize types that aren't natively supported, with LegalizeIntegerTypes.cpp and LegalizeFloatTypes.cpp handling specific type categories, and (5) FunctionLoweringInfo.cpp bridging the Function-level IR types to machine-level register assignments.",
